OL,3,CFormer mining areas still face
OL,4,Cshortage of quality jobs, report finds
OL,6,FThe report found that although there
OL,7,Fhas been substantial job growth in the
OL,8,Fformer coalfields, the rate of growth
OL,9,Fhas been slower than in the main
OL,10,Fregional cities. In the former mining
OL,11,Fcommunities, warehouse work has become
OL,12,Fthe dominant employer.
OL,14,FThe figures show that in the former
OL,15,Fcoalfields, there are only 57 employee
OL,16,Fjobs for every 100 residents of
OL,17,Fworking age, compared to a national
OL,18,Faverage of 73 jobs per 100, and 88 per
OL,19,F100 in the main regional cities.
