OL,3,CFormer mining areas still face
OL,4,Cshortage of quality jobs, report finds
OL,6,FThe shortage of local jobs means that
OL,7,Fmany coalfield residents commute to
OL,8,Fneighbouring towns and cities instead.
OL,9,FAverage hourly earnings are also 6-7%
OL,10,Fbelow the national average.
OL,12,FThe report argues that because of the
OL,13,Fsituation, many young people are
OL,14,Fhaving to move away from the
OL,15,Fcommunities in which they grew up to
OL,16,Fseek better opportunities elsewhere,
OL,17,Fleaving behind a population which is
OL,18,F"generally older and in poorer health."
